events.1889: Bangui founded as a French military post.
events.1910: Bangui becomes the capital of French Equatorial Africa.
events.1960: Central African Republic gains independence from France; Bangui remains capital.
events.1976: Jean-Bédel Bokassa declares himself emperor; Bangui becomes the capital of the Central African Empire.
events.1981: Central African Republic restored; Bangui remains capital.
events.1996: Bangui Peace Accord signed to end the First Central African Republic Civil War.
events.2003: Beginning of the Second Central African Republic Civil War.
events.2013: Séléka rebel coalition seizes Bangui; Michel Djotodia declares himself president.
events.2014: Djotodia resigns under international pressure; Catherine Samba-Panza becomes interim president.
events.2016: Faustin-Archange Touadéra elected president in a democratic election.
events.2021: Ongoing political instability and violence in Bangui and the Central African Republic.
